<br>
<a name=3D"negativenumber"> </a>
<br>
</li>




	</ol>=20
</li>

<li>  A Negative Number: <br>=20
To calculate the square root of a negative number, find the square root of =
the same positive number and multiply by "i".  ( where i represents an imag=
inary number and i =3D square root of -1) <br>=20

<em>Example</em>: square root of -5 <br> =20
=3D (square root of 5) x (square root of -1)<br>=20
=3D (square root of 5) x (i) <br>=20
=3D 2.236068 x i <br>=20
=3D 2.236068i <br>
<a name=3D"imaginarynumber"> </a>=20
<br>
</li>


<li> An Imaginary Number: <br> =20
	To calculate the square root of an imaginary number, find the square root =
of the number as if it were a real number (without the i) and then multiply=
 by the square root of i (where the square root of i =3D 0.7071068 + 0.7071=
068i) <br>


<em>Example</em>: 	square root of 5i <br>=20
=3D (square root of 5) x (square root of i) <br> =20
=3D (2.236068) x (0.7071068 + 0.7071068i) <br>=20
=3D 1.5811388 + 1.5811388i <br>
<a name=3D"complexnumber"> </a>
<br>=20
</li>

<li> A Complex Number: <br>=20
To find the square root of a complex number, use the following equation: <b=
r>=20

Square root (a + bi) =3D c + di <br>=20
Where: <br>
c =3D (1/square root of 2) x square root of [ (square root of(a<sup>2</sup>=
+b<sup>2</sup>)) + a ] <br>=20
d =3D (sign of b/square root of 2) x square root of [ (square root of(a<sup=
>2</sup>+b<sup>2</sup>)) - a ] <br>


<em>Example</em>: the square root of 3-5i =3D c + di <br>=20
c =3D (1/square root of 2) x square root of [ (square root of(3<sup>2</sup>=
+(-5)<sup>2</sup>)) + 3 ] <br>=20
c =3D 2.1013034 <br>
d =3D (-1/square root of 2) x square root of [ (square root of(3<sup>2</sup=
>+(-5)<sup>2</sup>)) - 3 ] <br>
d =3D -1.1897378 <br>
Thus: square root of 3-5i =3D 2.1013034 - 1.1897378i <br>


</li>
</ol>


<br>
<br>












<h3>Need to calculate the square root of a number with a handheld calculato=
r or looking to buy a new calculator?</h3>=20
<p>=20

